    • Field Detail

      • names

        public java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> names
        The accepted dataset names. If null all dataset names are accepted.

      • providers

        public java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> providers
        The accepted dataset providers. If null all providers are accepted.

      • datasetTypes

        public java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> datasetTypes
        The accepted dataset types. If null all types are accepted.

      • imageryTypes

        public java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> imageryTypes
        The accepted imagery types. If null all types are accepted. If non-null only those datasets that contain one or more of the specified imagery types are accepted.

      • spatialFilter

        public RasterDataStore.DatasetQueryParameters.SpatialFilter spatialFilter
        The spatial filter to be applied to the results. If non-null, only those datasets that satisfy the criteria of the spatial filter will be returned.

      • minGsd

        public double minGsd
        The minimum GSD (resolution in meters-per-pixel). Any datasets with a maximum resolution that is lower than the specified value will be excluded (e.g. 10m data has a lower resolution than 5m data). A value of Double.NaN may be specified to indicate that there is no minimum GSD constraint.

      • maxGsd

        public double maxGsd
        The maximum GSD (resolution in meters-per-pixel). Any datasets with a minimum resolution that is greater than the specified value will be excluded (e.g. 5m data has a higher resolution than 10m data). A value of Double.NaN may be specified to indicate that there is no maximum GSD constraint.

      • remoteLocalFlag

        public RasterDataStore.DatasetQueryParameters.RemoteLocalFlag remoteLocalFlag
        A flag indicating whether or not remote or local datasets should be selected. If null all datasets may be selected.

      • order

        public java.util.Collection<RasterDataStore.DatasetQueryParameters.Order> order
        The ordering parameters, may be null to indicate no ordering. An argument containing RasterDataStore.DatasetQueryParameters.GSD and RasterDataStore.DatasetQueryParameters.Name would order the results first by resolution, and, in the event that the resolution was equal, by dataset name. Note that the order of the fields will be important.

      • limit

        public int limit
        The limit on the number of results returned. If 0 there shall be no limit.

      • offset

        public int offset
        The offset into the result list. This argument is only applicable if limit is greater-than 0.

      • intersect

        public void intersect​(RasterDataStore.DatasetQueryParameters other)
        Intersects this RasterDataStore.DatasetQueryParameters with another instance. Intersection will be performed such that if a particular field is defined by only of of this or b, the defined field will be accepted. If a field is defined by both this and b, the field will be modified such that it is the intersection or more restrictive of the two. In this manner, this can be used as a filter on b.
